--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Zack Widup &lt;w9sz@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; 
&gt; The chip is a microcontroller.  It needs a program 
called &quot;firmware&quot; put 
&gt; into it before it will do anything useful.  The chips have a 
program 
&gt; memory which comes blank when you buy them.
&gt; 
&gt; The &quot;code&quot; is the representation of what is called machine language 
&gt; that tells the various parts of the microcontroller what to do.  In 
this 
&gt; case, I imagine it increases a voltage with a certain pattern and 
then 
&gt; drops it down to zero, starting over again and repeating at a 
certain 
&gt; rate. This would produce a repetitive sweep of the radio at a 
certain rate 
&gt; when the microcontroller is hooked up to the radio correctly.
&gt; 
&gt; It wouldn&#39;t be difficult for me to write my own program to do this 
with a 
&gt; PIC microcontroller, but if someone else has already done it, why 
bother?
&gt; 
&gt; If I can&#39;t get my hands on the machine code, I&#39;ll write some myself.
&gt; 
